JOHANNESBURG – The Land Bank has weathered a tough economic environment in its first half-year performance. The agricultural lender’s profits grew by over 70-percent to about R57-million -that's R33-million higher than the same period last year. READ: Land Bank to transform farming ownership in SA It attributes the jump in profits to higher interest and investment income, and lower debt write-downs. The Land Bank said the asset quality on its loan book continues to improve. In September, it raised an R1-billion in a bond auction. eNCA